      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Justification of continuum mechanics assumptions, contact formulation, and material constitutive model selection documented and peer-reviewed.",
      "rationale": "The ensemble uses a nonlinear elastic-plastic constitutive model (bilinear isotropic hardening) for Ti-6Al-4V ELI, consistent with published material characterization data. Contact between screw and block is modeled with penalty-based frictional contact (mu=0.2). Model form assumptions are documented in the V&V report and reviewed by an independent biomechanics expert. Gradation 3 achieved."
