      "rationale": "N=11 non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs tested across two independent laboratories. All specimens sourced from production lots with full dimensional inspection (CMM) confirming conformance to design nominal within ±0.05 mm. Traceability documentation archived. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions span the intended operating range; at minimum two distinct load levels or environmental conditions tested.",
      "rationale": "Testing was conducted under a single ASTM F1717 quasi-static compression-bending condition (5 mm/min displacement rate, ambient temperature). Only one test condition was evaluated; the required level of 3 is not achieved. This is a documented limitation of the validation dataset. The achieved level of 2 reflects that test conditions are well-characterized and controlled, but lack of multi-condition coverage prevents Gradation 3. This factor is below the required level; risk is accepted given that the ASTM F1717 protocol is the sole regulatory-relevant condition for this device."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
